Jake Green.

02:07.038 --> 02:08.592
How you doing, man?

02:09.634 --> 02:11.642
--When did you get back
to town? --Just now.

02:12.458 --> 02:13.220
Is that Bonnie?

02:14.437 --> 02:15.923
You grew up.

02:16.765 --> 02:18.130
Wait a minute, where
the hell you been?

02:19.218 --> 02:20.311
You know, around.

02:20.788 --> 02:24.341
--Jake, no one's been around
for five years. --The Army.

02:24.597 --> 02:27.150
--I've been in the
Army. --Good for you.

02:28.237 --> 02:30.533
--Who's that?
--She's from the IRS.

02:31.466 --> 02:33.331
--IRS? Audit
IRS? --Yeah.

02:34.156 --> 02:37.043
--Not going well?
--No. Forget it.

02:37.048 --> 02:40.080
How about you and I, we go
out tonight and we catch up?

02:40.088 --> 02:42.383
I'd love to, but I just came
in to see my grandfather, and

02:42.708 --> 02:44.611
--I've got to get
back, so... --Okay.

02:45.946 --> 02:46.721
Bonnie.

02:50.325 --> 02:52.733
Bonnie, we need a pie.
One strawberry rhubarb.

02:55.547 --> 02:57.531
Welcome back to
Jericho, Jake.

03:01.105 --> 03:02.400
His wife is lovely,

03:02.527 --> 03:04.233
but I don't
know about him.

03:04.588 --> 03:07.580
Mrs. Olsen made me
promise not to tell,

03:07.587 --> 03:11.033
but she heard that he bought
the old Thompson place in cash.

03:11.508 --> 03:12.433
Cash.

03:14.157 --> 03:17.271
--That color looks really
good on you. --I know.

03:18.247 --> 03:21.631
--Why didn't your mom take you to
New York? --'Cause she hates me.

03:23.586 --> 03:25.333
What are you
looking at, loser?

03:29.856 --> 03:33.282
I could be shopping in SoHo right
now instead of Gracie's Market.

03:33.288 --> 03:34.653
--I know. Look at
this thing-- --so ugly.

03:35.597 --> 03:38.473
--Promise not to tell?
--Promise, Mrs. Leigh.

03:38.678 --> 03:40.073
What about you, Jake?

03:40.196 --> 03:41.680
Where have you been
keeping yourself?

03:42.546 --> 03:44.412
I've been playing
minor league baseball.

03:44.956 --> 03:47.113
Oh, is that a fact?

03:47.838 --> 03:48.652
Well...

03:49.165 --> 03:50.601
when do you get
in from Chicago?

03:52.317 --> 03:53.091
All right.

03:53.926 --> 03:55.633
Good. I'll pick you up.

04:01.598 --> 04:02.731
I love you, too.

04:06.396 --> 04:09.231
--Hey. --Sorry,
hi. Um...

04:10.166 --> 04:11.130
What are you doing here?

04:11.616 --> 04:14.891
I just came in for the day
to visit my grandfather,

04:14.896 --> 04:17.690
--see the family.
--Yeah, of course, sure.

04:17.718 --> 04:20.913
--I just didn't hear.
--Anyway, how you been?

04:21.538 --> 04:23.211
Mom tells me you're teaching
at the high school now.

04:24.136 --> 04:26.230
--Yeah, it's
weird, huh? --Yeah.

04:26.458 --> 04:27.113
I love it.

04:28.106 --> 04:29.851
I just bought a
house in the Pines.

04:30.597 --> 04:32.402
The East Side on
a teacher's salary?

04:33.507 --> 04:35.040
Uh, my-my fianc?

04:35.156 --> 04:37.300
he's in banking, so...

04:38.428 --> 04:42.272
--Oh, that helps. --Yeah,
Roger really loves it here.

04:45.326 --> 04:46.863
Well, I'm happy
for you, Emily.

04:47.446 --> 04:49.630
--How about you, you
got somebody? --No.

04:52.088 --> 04:54.890
--I'm sorry, I shouldn't...
--No, you're not, you love it.

04:59.337 --> 05:02.841
--Where have you
been? --The Navy.

05:06.467 --> 05:08.051
Oh, why do I even bother?

05:08.727 --> 05:09.590
Seriously...

05:10.537 --> 05:11.972
where have you been?

05:12.916 --> 05:17.041
(And you ask me what
I want this year)

05:17.047 --> 05:21.250
(And I try to make
this kind and clear)

05:21.537 --> 05:28.943
(Just a chance that maybe
we'll find better days )

05:29.608 --> 05:34.242
('Cause I don't need
boxes wrapped in strings)

05:34.248 --> 05:38.212
(And desire and love
and empty things)

05:38.216 --> 05:47.102
(Just a chance that maybe
we'll find better days)

05:47.105 --> 05:50.710
(So take these words..)

05:49.056 --> 05:50.762
Oh, Jake!

05:51.327 --> 05:52.373
Oh, honey!

05:52.928 --> 05:56.272
--Oh, you're home!
--You're choking me, Mom.

05:57.278 --> 05:58.813
I thought I heard
an annoying voice.

05:58.978 --> 06:01.621
--Hey, brother.
--Good to see you.

06:03.827 --> 06:09.181
('Cause tonight's the night
the world begins again.)

06:09.187 --> 06:11.092
I'm not here to interfere
with your campaign, Dad.

06:11.096 --> 06:12.463
All I want is
your signature,

06:12.468 --> 06:13.592
then I'll
visit Grandpa...

06:13.728 --> 06:14.823
After five years, Jake,

06:14.827 --> 06:15.992
that's all you
have to say to Dad?

06:15.995 --> 06:19.621
--It's none of your business, Eric. --It
is his business, it is all our business.

06:19.626 --> 06:22.203
--What you put this family
through... --Johnston. For god's sake.

06:22.205 --> 06:25.081
--Now, he could've been... --We could spend a
week talking about what I could've been, all right?

06:25.087 --> 06:25.973
I've apologized.

06:26.085 --> 06:27.252
I've made amends.

06:27.917 --> 06:28.892
This is me now.

06:29.395 --> 06:32.263
--I have a plan, but I need my money to
make a clean start. --It's not your money,

06:32.268 --> 06:35.181
--it's your grandfather's money. --I
know, but he gave it to me for a reason.

06:35.186 --> 06:37.830
And he gave me authority
over it for a reason.

06:40.227 --> 06:44.002
--You convince me you're leading a more
productive life and then... --That's right, Jake.

06:44.436 --> 06:45.763
We were both born
on third base.

06:45.888 --> 06:47.591
Quit pretending
you hit a triple.

06:50.856 --> 06:54.893
--Now, when are you going to realize
I'm 32-years-old. --When you do.

07:00.717 --> 07:03.390
Can I talk to my
mayor then, huh?

07:07.096 --> 07:08.920
Let's go see
your grandfather.

07:13.488 --> 07:15.931
--I just...
--Stop it, Jake.

07:15.935 --> 07:18.362
--The one thing I can't... --You
would have been here if you could.

07:30.406 --> 07:31.390
I brought money.

07:31.917 --> 07:33.861
--Here. --I
can't, Mom.

07:35.306 --> 07:37.682
--I'll talk to your
father. --He doesn't get it.

07:38.616 --> 07:41.432
--Because you won't tell him why
you really need the money. --Mom.

07:41.435 --> 07:43.061
You don't give
him enough credit.

07:43.138 --> 07:46.102
--Your dad's had a few trials of his
own, you know? --He can never know.

07:52.728 --> 07:53.700
Just...

07:53.887 --> 07:57.611
--Stay one more day. --I got to
get back to San Diego by tomorrow.

08:02.376 --> 08:04.472
--Mom, one more
thing. --Hmm?

08:08.227 --> 08:09.790
You have clumsy hands.

08:12.356 --> 08:13.482
I love you.

08:13.746 --> 08:15.530
Be careful now, okay?

08:33.996 --> 08:37.863
Mr. Speaker, the President
of the United States.

08:39.976 --> 08:42.539
