09:36.009 --> 09:37.033
...carried on...

09:45.238 --> 09:46.200
We have...

09:57.207 --> 09:58.532
No fun, Woody.

09:58.665 --> 10:00.873
You have to hide better!

10:08.917 --> 10:10.002
Woody?

10:11.728 --> 10:13.162
What are you looking at?

10:56.118 --> 10:57.243
Look! Look it!

11:01.585 --> 11:02.813
Hurry on there right now.

11:03.287 --> 11:05.081
Yeah, you better hurry
up and get on home then.

11:05.088 --> 11:05.941
Where's Cody?!

11:05.988 --> 11:07.903
Has anyone seen Cody?

11:08.437 --> 11:09.602
We haven't got time.

11:20.355 --> 11:21.832
Shh.

11:22.697 --> 11:25.281
Gail, what's going on?

11:27.516 --> 11:28.871
Oh, Johnston.

11:32.768 --> 11:33.552
Nothing.

11:34.608 --> 11:36.833
All right, it looks like the
explosion came from the west,

11:36.838 --> 11:37.421
maybe Denver.

11:37.508 --> 11:39.140
Jimmy, get on the radio.

11:39.148 --> 11:40.553
I want everybody at
the sheriff's station.

11:40.556 --> 11:42.552
--I'll pick up Eric.
Let's move. --All right.

11:42.558 --> 11:44.041
Dad, don't leave.

11:46.126 --> 11:46.980
Come here.

11:52.796 --> 11:54.350
I'll be back real
soon, all right?

11:59.455 --> 12:00.580
Johnston.

12:03.276 --> 12:04.320
Jake.

12:06.297 --> 12:07.501
We'll find him.

12:41.225 --> 12:42.071
We're bringing them
out of the mine,

12:42.076 --> 12:43.520
five at a time
like always.

12:43.527 --> 12:44.881
No need to start a panic.

12:44.887 --> 12:48.191
--You're just trying to get another hour's
work out of my men! --Stop it, the both of you.

12:48.865 --> 12:52.023
Norman, get everybody out
of the mine immediately.

12:52.025 --> 12:53.973
And Shep, help
him for a change.

12:55.695 --> 12:57.441
--Sheriff?
Chief? --Yeah?

12:57.448 --> 13:00.592
--Damage, fires, buildings?
--Nothing, Mr. Mayor.

13:00.595 --> 13:02.342
--The town's fine. --Well,
let's hope you're right.

13:02.395 --> 13:03.283
What does that mean?

13:05.265 --> 13:06.942
Do we have any
Geiger counters?

13:11.835 --> 13:12.550
Excuse me?

13:12.728 --> 13:13.470
Uh, excuse me.

13:13.477 --> 13:15.152
Did something happen?

13:15.936 --> 13:17.923
So, what does the
emergency plan say?

13:18.588 --> 13:21.342
Contact the governor, National
Guard and state troopers.

13:21.696 --> 13:25.823
--Are we under attack? --Son, I
don't want to hear that word again.

13:26.337 --> 13:27.561
Now look, this could
have been a test.

13:27.568 --> 13:28.552
It could have
been an accident.

13:28.556 --> 13:31.003
There's, uh, military
bases near Denver.

13:31.597 --> 13:34.123
One explosion does
not make an attack.

13:35.685 --> 13:36.623
If we stay calm,

13:36.817 --> 13:38.242
the town stays
calm, okay?

13:59.266 --> 14:00.271
Oh.

14:00.986 --> 14:02.790
--I found the Geiger
counters. --Thanks.

14:03.097 --> 14:04.543
Oh, Grey, good
to see you.

14:04.595 --> 14:07.193
--We can use the extra help.
--Well, thank you, Johnston, Eric.

14:07.397 --> 14:10.702
--Well, what can I do to
help? --We'll let you know.

14:14.917 --> 14:15.990
Does it work, Dad?

14:18.218 --> 14:19.280
Looks okay.

14:19.286 --> 14:20.330
Mr. Mayor.

14:20.766 --> 14:25.312
--Sheriff-- the bomb? --Yes, ma'am, so
far there's no sign of any radiation.

14:25.316 --> 14:27.492
--We'll keep checking
around town. --No. No, sir.

14:28.165 --> 14:31.741
The school bus isn't back from
the field trip with my daughter.

14:34.217 --> 14:36.442
--Well, do
something! --I got it.

14:36.917 --> 14:39.593
--You-You should be out there looking
for Stacy. --Yes, ma'am. Ma'am, Teresa,

14:39.598 --> 14:41.420
this is the first
we've heard of it,

14:41.628 --> 14:42.903
but we will deal
with it, all right?

14:42.907 --> 14:45.913
--Just please don't worry.
--That's easy for you to say.

14:46.775 --> 14:48.522
You don't have a
child out there.

15:36.417 --> 15:38.782
So the school bus
was here at the caves.

15:38.788 --> 15:40.853
Now, who can tell me where they
might have gone for repairs?

15:40.858 --> 15:44.472
--Well, there's Wilson's garage
off 160. --Or Cedar Run Road.

15:44.478 --> 15:46.411
Principal Movey said
they took a detour

15:46.415 --> 15:47.541
before the phone cut out.

15:47.738 --> 15:48.843
Well, I figure two teams.

15:48.845 --> 15:50.511
There's only so many
places they could be.

15:50.516 --> 15:52.892
--Now, what about the
parents? --Right, right.

15:54.668 --> 15:57.872
Folks. Folks! Folks.

16:00.607 --> 16:04.581
Now, look, I know that every part
of you wantsto just rush out there.

16:04.585 --> 16:05.590
I don't blame you.

16:06.617 --> 16:09.413
But as your friend, I'm
asking you to think about that.

16:10.416 --> 16:11.460
You're safe here.

16:12.288 --> 16:14.232
Now, what if, God forbid,

16:14.935 --> 16:16.593
you go out there,
and you get stranded,

16:16.598 --> 16:18.582
and your child
comes back an orphan?

16:19.788 --> 16:20.930
You know the
sheriff and his men.

16:20.936 --> 16:23.701
You know they'll find
your kids, so please.

16:33.656 --> 16:34.460
Help!

16:37.517 --> 16:38.413
Mister!

16:40.826 --> 16:42.190
Mister, please!

16:43.165 --> 16:44.060
Mister!

16:44.888 --> 16:45.933
What? What is it?

16:47.276 --> 16:48.750
Mister, help!

16:49.375 --> 16:51.103
--Mister, please!
--I think they're...

16:51.245 --> 16:52.523
I think they're dying!

17:06.608 --> 17:07.502
That's fine.

17:14.694 --> 17:15.369
Let's go find out.

17:15.377 --> 17:17.859
Jimmy, get over there
and calm those folks down.

17:19.015 --> 17:20.602
Hey, Pete, come on!

17:20.605 --> 17:22.441
We have our
frequencies, sir,

17:23.588 --> 17:25.880
but outside, it's like
there's no one there.

17:26.358 --> 17:27.290
All right, um...

17:27.928 --> 17:28.900
what about analog?

17:28.907 --> 17:31.723
We could contact the governor
with a Ham radio, couldn't we?

17:31.728 --> 17:34.532
That could work, but there's
only one in town that I know of.

17:35.398 --> 17:37.341
I was afraid you were
going to say that.

17:38.356 --> 17:40.583
Excuse me, Sheriff?

17:40.876 --> 17:42.000
Robert Hawkins.

17:42.108 --> 17:43.461
Well, it's good to
meet you, Mr. Hawkins,

17:43.468 --> 17:45.193
but as you can see,
we've got our hands full.

17:45.196 --> 17:46.521
Could you use
an extra man?

17:46.526 --> 17:48.190
No civilians,
mayor's orders.

17:48.325 --> 17:51.210
But I used to be
a cop-- St. Louis.

17:51.825 --> 17:55.493
--Do you know the roads around
here? --No, just moved to town.

17:55.495 --> 17:58.353
Then I'm afraid you'd just
slow us down, I'm sorry.

17:59.805 --> 18:01.943
You might want to get
some black spray paint.

18:04.285 --> 18:06.380
You know, cover that?

18:07.386 --> 18:09.680
Look, I know you're telling
people it was an accident,

18:10.156 --> 18:11.470
and I hope it was,

18:12.687 --> 18:14.793
but if it was an
attack, Sheriff,

18:14.966 --> 18:16.482
and there's
chaos out there,

18:17.225 --> 18:18.711
you might not want the
wrong people knowing

18:18.716 --> 18:20.282
that Jericho
is still here.

18:21.186 --> 18:24.142
With all due
respect, Mr. Hawkins,

18:24.517 --> 18:26.260
this is not St. Louis.

18:31.857 --> 18:33.473
--Dad, are you okay?
--Yeah, I'm fine.

18:33.475 --> 18:34.531
Don't worry about me.

18:35.747 --> 18:38.271
Oh, Oliver, would
you stop that?

18:39.887 --> 18:41.363
Sorry, Johnston.

18:42.296 --> 18:43.623
Thought you were aliens.

18:44.095 --> 18:47.190
Well, we're under attack
by aliens, don't you know?

18:47.195 --> 18:48.591
Yes, we do. That's
why we're here.

18:48.996 --> 18:52.352
--Do you have your
Ham radio? --Yeah.

18:53.567 --> 18:57.001
--For you, 50
cents. --Oliver.

18:57.227 --> 19:02.761
--Well, I need my
50 cents. --Okay.

19:03.908 --> 19:05.542
Let me get you change.

