okay? --Yeah.

21:08.935 --> 21:11.513
I think my leg is broken.

21:11.975 --> 21:14.481
--Can you feel
your toes? --Yeah.

21:15.535 --> 21:16.822
Don't worry about me.

21:17.125 --> 21:18.251
Worry about them.

21:20.516 --> 21:21.640
Is anybody hurt?

21:21.866 --> 21:23.220
Huh? Anybody?

21:24.508 --> 21:25.670
Stacy's sick.

21:26.067 --> 21:27.201
She can't breathe.

21:32.285 --> 21:33.181
What's wrong?

21:33.618 --> 21:34.770
What happened?

21:34.795 --> 21:35.691
When the bus stopped,

21:35.697 --> 21:36.780
she was like this.

21:39.087 --> 21:40.420
It's okay,
Stacy, let me see.

21:40.708 --> 21:41.482
Let me see it?

21:43.436 --> 21:44.370
Can I see?

21:44.506 --> 21:45.223
Let me just see, Stacy.

21:45.396 --> 21:47.291
It's okay. It's okay.

21:49.656 --> 21:50.932
Do you have an ice pack?

21:51.106 --> 21:52.790
We've got to stop
the swelling now.

21:53.508 --> 21:56.220
Lucas, the first aid
kit is under the seat.

21:57.038 --> 21:57.811
You're okay.

21:58.557 --> 22:00.610
Come on, it's all right.

22:00.646 --> 22:01.350
Just keep breathing.

22:01.445 --> 22:02.721
Breathe normally,
all right?

22:02.786 --> 22:04.930
It's okay. It's
okay, you're fine.

22:04.935 --> 22:06.250
Just keep
breathing normally.

22:08.987 --> 22:10.360
Okay, you're okay.

22:10.667 --> 22:11.721
You're okay.

22:13.855 --> 22:14.781
Please.

22:15.676 --> 22:17.693
Calm down, calm down.

22:18.108 --> 22:20.532
Hey? Hey, Stacy?

22:20.776 --> 22:22.732
No, no, no. No.

22:43.467 --> 22:45.800
Think. Think.

22:45.978 --> 22:46.903
Think.

22:48.787 --> 22:49.603
All right.

22:49.607 --> 22:50.711
Look, I need everyone's
help right now.

22:50.718 --> 22:51.610
Who has a pen?

22:51.617 --> 22:52.280
Does anyone?

22:53.577 --> 22:54.520
Does anybody have a pen?

22:54.525 --> 22:55.733
All right, I need a pen.

22:55.735 --> 22:57.961
--We have pencils.
--No, I need a tube.

22:57.966 --> 22:59.181
Something hollow, um...

22:59.188 --> 23:00.080
A straw.

23:00.175 --> 23:01.460
--I have a straw.
--Here, let me see it.

23:01.465 --> 23:02.431
Let me see it, come on.

23:03.518 --> 23:04.491
That's too thin.

23:04.748 --> 23:06.300
Does anyone else
have a juice box?

23:06.267 --> 23:07.383
--I do! --All right, get
them out, get them out.

23:07.388 --> 23:08.320
Get some Band-Aids out.

23:08.328 --> 23:09.332
--What's your
name? --Julie.

23:09.336 --> 23:10.732
All right, everybody
give your straws to Julie.

23:10.735 --> 23:12.183
Okay? Hurry, quick.

23:12.498 --> 23:13.660
Make them into a circle.

23:14.616 --> 23:15.823
All right, you got that?

23:16.787 --> 23:19.032
There you go, now tape them
together with those Band-Aids.

23:20.648 --> 23:21.851
Come on, Stacy.

23:26.207 --> 23:27.533
All right, who's
the strongest kid?

23:28.407 --> 23:30.203
You. I need you to
hold her shoulders down,

23:30.206 --> 23:31.222
in case she wakes
up. All right?

23:31.895 --> 23:32.901
Don't look.

23:45.255 --> 23:46.420
Where's my straws?

23:56.497 --> 23:57.473
Come on, come on.

24:00.396 --> 24:03.310
Breathe for me,
okay? Please?

24:03.635 --> 24:04.873
Come on. Come on.

24:41.027 --> 24:42.503
Wait, I see something.

24:42.956 --> 24:46.351
--Okay, okay, we see
the bus. --Uh, good.

24:46.358 --> 24:49.550
--You want us? --No, no,
you keep looking for Jake.

24:54.865 --> 24:56.313
Let's get down
there, boys.

25:00.175 --> 25:02.272
How'd you learn
how to do that?

25:02.988 --> 25:04.931
Uh, military school.

25:05.845 --> 25:07.693
Were you a soldier?

25:09.458 --> 25:11.360
No, a screw up.

25:34.206 --> 25:35.222
Sheriff.

25:35.687 --> 25:36.733
Sheriff, look at this.

25:37.236 --> 25:38.411
It's the wrong bus!

25:38.416 --> 25:40.911
Riley, Riley
get over here!

25:41.656 --> 25:42.702
Riley!

25:52.908 --> 25:54.192
Oh, great.

25:54.356 --> 25:56.262
Where's the damn
rescue party?

25:57.786 --> 25:59.221
Oh, hi, Dale.

25:59.847 --> 26:01.340
Come on in, honey.

26:01.347 --> 26:03.991
Come on, we're all trying
to get through this together.

26:07.425 --> 26:08.513
Hi, Dale.

26:09.765 --> 26:10.853
You okay, honey?

26:13.707 --> 26:14.601
What you got there?

26:17.917 --> 26:18.963
It's my mom.

26:20.826 --> 26:23.292
Hi, Dale, sorry I
didn't call sooner, Angel

26:23.295 --> 26:25.821
but we decided to stay in
the city an extra couple days.

26:25.827 --> 26:29.211
--Put down the phone and come to
bed. --Honey, stop that, it's my kid.

26:30.006 --> 26:31.802
Baby, what are you
staring at out the window?

26:31.807 --> 26:33.292
Get over here
and look at this!

26:33.728 --> 26:35.290
What, what is that?

26:35.886 --> 26:37.981
Oh, my God, oh, my God.

26:46.878 --> 26:49.091
Oh, Dale, I am so sorry.

26:49.607 --> 26:51.621
I didn't know your
mother was in Denver.

26:53.395 --> 26:54.641
She wasn't in Denver.

26:55.755 --> 26:56.611
She was in Atlanta.

26:57.266 --> 26:59.292
Oh, my God.

27:05.236 --> 27:07.761
I'm sure that they'll
have some answers.

27:10.077 --> 27:11.071
Oh, my God.

27:16.185 --> 27:17.041
How is she?

27:17.147 --> 27:18.541
We have to get her back.

27:32.106 --> 27:33.362
Right here. Right here.

27:35.018 --> 27:38.982
Miss Lisinski, are we going
to have school tomorrow?

27:40.396 --> 27:41.792
We'll figure
it out, honey.

27:42.695 --> 27:43.791
I vote no.

27:50.576 --> 27:52.832
Dale, Dale, what
are you doing, honey?

27:53.456 --> 27:55.440
Please, please
don't steal from me.

27:55.747 --> 27:56.643
Dale!

28:00.326 --> 28:01.682
--Ready?
--Yeah, yeah.

28:02.768 --> 28:03.892
Hey, you got extra there?

28:03.897 --> 28:05.311
First come, first serve.

28:06.457 --> 28:07.971
You filled up your truck, you
going to mow your lawn, too?

28:07.977 --> 28:10.293
--I've got a family, you
know? --We've all got families.

28:10.296 --> 28:10.871
Come on.

28:11.778 --> 28:12.930
Get your hand
off the can.

28:13.756 --> 28:14.612
Come on.

28:14.987 --> 28:16.771
What do you think
you're doing, hmm?

28:17.246 --> 28:18.400
--What are you doing?
--What's your problem?

28:20.828 --> 28:22.160
All right,
everybody sit down.

28:37.748 --> 28:38.642
Hurry.

28:48.797 --> 28:51.401
Food won't go rotten as long
as the weather stays cool.

28:51.756 --> 28:53.742
Hopefully the power
will be fixed by then.

28:54.568 --> 28:56.082
Thank you for this, Dale.

28:57.766 --> 28:59.040
Anything for you, ma'am.

29:04.918 --> 29:07.482
--Step away from the
car. --Get out of the car.

29:09.308 --> 29:11.403
--Hey, hey, hey, hey,
come on, --break it up.

29:11.406 --> 29:13.220
Get off.

29:13.227 --> 29:14.612
You need to get
some lights on

29:14.888 --> 29:16.883
before people
start losing it.

29:16.887 --> 29:18.641
All we have is lanterns
and flashlights.

29:18.648 --> 29:20.512
That's not enough to
light up the street though.

29:20.828 --> 29:23.541
But your town does
roadwork at night, right?

29:27.908 --> 29:28.763
Excuse me.

29:30.407 --> 29:33.341
--The machine doesn't work. --Well,
you guys have to pay cash or something!

29:40.995 --> 29:42.583
You sure you're not
the science teacher?

29:42.906 --> 29:45.673
Chief, we got a little problem
down here at the gas station.

29:45.676 --> 29:47.151
We need your
help right away.

29:48.566 --> 29:50.360
--I'm on my way.
--I got this.

29:50.495 --> 29:52.640
--I'll come with you.
--All right, thanks.

29:53.615 --> 29:54.351
Sir.

29:54.877 --> 29:56.371
Something's going on
at the gas station.

29:56.557 --> 29:57.101
Big crowd.

29:57.228 --> 29:58.233
Looks like trouble.

29:58.747 --> 29:59.832
Gonna need
help down here.

30:00.965 --> 30:02.053
--Dad.
--I heard.

30:02.056 --> 30:03.110
Go, go.

30:05.666 --> 30:06.803
--Sara?
--It's okay.

30:07.018 --> 30:07.602
Honey?

30:07.915 --> 30:09.380
I don't have
time right now.

30:09.386 --> 30:10.900
--Some damn
fool... --Johnston.

30:10.908 --> 30:12.772
--What?
--Listen to me.

30:13.948 --> 30:17.880
Dale Turner's mother died
tonight in another explosion.

30:20.338 --> 30:21.903
Atlanta.

30:24.466 --> 30:25.793
Oh, my God.

30:47.467 --> 30:48.320
Sheriff?

30:48.485 --> 30:49.593
Yeah, there's no
sign of Jake out here

30:49.595 --> 30:52.122
in fact, there's, uh,
no sign of anybody.

30:52.818 --> 30:53.302
We're going to,

30:53.307 --> 30:54.400
we're going to head back.

30:54.827 --> 30:56.693
Let me know if the
kids need anything

30:57.027 --> 30:57.922
Sheriff, you there?

30:59.217 --> 31:00.340
Stay awake.

31:01.138 --> 31:02.611
Stay awake,
don't--

31:06.685 --> 31:08.520
Does this bus
have a gas can?

31:13.036 --> 31:14.210
If the bus...

31:15.887 --> 31:17.213
If it stops...

31:18.456 --> 31:19.271
Okay.

31:22.926 --> 31:24.681
Kids, listen to me.

31:26.475 --> 31:28.012
If the bus stops again,

31:28.837 --> 31:31.793
we're going to need
you to walk back to town

31:32.235 --> 31:34.180
and get help, okay?

31:35.057 --> 31:36.530
I don't know
where we are.

31:37.238 --> 31:38.533
When we get to
the stop sign,

31:39.196 --> 31:40.321
turn left, all right?

31:40.328 --> 31:41.183
Take a left.

31:42.018 --> 31:43.181
Which way is left?

31:45.256 --> 31:46.850
Hold up your hands...

31:48.686 --> 31:50.010
stick out your thumbs.

31:51.615 --> 31:53.330
The one that makes the L,

31:54.116 --> 31:55.403
that's your left.

32:08.665 --> 32:09.950
Get your hands off me!

32:17.375 --> 32:18.581
Do something, will you?

32:21.938 --> 32:23.880
County Edwards!
Carl! Carl!

32:27.376 --> 32:28.960
Stop it right now!

32:30.015 --> 32:32.283
Yeah, Morty, I'm
talking to you!

32:34.795 --> 32:35.910
Michael Stevenson.

32:36.778 --> 32:38.331
Carl Meeks... Carl!

32:40.846 --> 32:42.793
Why are you turning
on each other?

32:43.415 --> 32:45.403
Stealing from
your neighbors?

32:46.458 --> 32:48.711
You are fighting
the wrong people!

32:50.085 --> 32:52.180
We are literally
in the dark.

32:53.007 --> 32:57.921
All I'm saying is that I-I
think we need to get organized.

32:58.436 --> 32:59.252
I...

33:01.597 --> 33:03.150
I don't know
where the mayor is,

33:03.628 --> 33:06.091
but maybe it's time we came
up with a plan ourselves.

33:06.278 --> 33:06.773
What's going on, Gray?

33:06.778 --> 33:07.942
We making speeches?

33:08.915 --> 33:11.292
With all due
respect, Mr. Mayor

33:11.298 --> 33:12.333
we have a missing bus,

33:12.578 --> 33:13.581
no police,

33:13.936 --> 33:15.960
firemen doing
policemen's job.

33:15.966 --> 33:17.522
--How dare you politicize
it! --Eric. Eric.

33:17.525 --> 33:19.002
I'm not talking
to my opponent

33:19.006 --> 33:20.642
I'm talking to my mayor.

33:21.047 --> 33:22.300
Now, I don't care
about the election

33:22.308 --> 33:23.471
I care about survival.

33:23.477 --> 33:25.160
We just might be
on our own here,

33:25.316 --> 33:28.042
and I need to know what
my mayor intends to do!

33:29.368 --> 33:31.501
Folks, I know we've been
through a lot tonight.

33:32.345 --> 33:32.940
I want to tell
you something.

33:32.947 --> 33:34.190
I've been to
big cities and

33:34.195 --> 33:35.232
I've been to
foreign countries,

33:35.235 --> 33:38.511
--but I will take the good people of-- --The
good people of Jericho over any other city

33:38.518 --> 33:40.472
we know, Mr. Mayor,
we've heard the speech.

33:40.478 --> 33:41.692
Well, Shep, I hope
you don't think

33:41.697 --> 33:43.370
I've been asleep
at the switch.

33:43.847 --> 33:46.801
We had all hoped
this was an accident

33:46.806 --> 33:49.061
but the
unfortunate truth is

33:49.067 --> 33:50.900
there was another
explosion in Atlanta.

33:50.907 --> 33:52.270
--What?
--Oh, my God.

33:52.595 --> 33:56.533
--I been busy trying to contact the governor.
--Yeah? Well, what if the governor's dead?

33:56.538 --> 33:59.932
There is no report of
anything happening in Topeka.

33:59.498 --> 34:01.923
--How are we going to get reports
without television? --Or no phones?

34:02.256 --> 34:03.303
What about New York?

34:03.305 --> 34:06.501
--We don't know anything about New York.
--When are we going to get the power back on?

34:06.265 --> 34:08.620
--Is the drinking water
okay? --One at a time, please.

34:08.985 --> 34:11.721
--Calm down. --Calm down?
My boy is still out there.

34:11.728 --> 34:13.071
The sheriff is
out there right now

34:13.076 --> 34:15.141
looking for your
boy and my boy.

34:15.148 --> 34:17.400
What if we had more
police officers out there?

34:17.065 --> 34:19.409
--We need to know what you're going
to do now. --No one can answer that.

34:38.467 --> 34:40.960
Help them! Help them!

34:41.215 --> 34:42.101
It's Stacy.

34:43.466 --> 34:44.793
Hey, there, little one.

34:45.398 --> 34:47.721
--You're okay.
--I got you.

34:50.067 --> 34:51.112
What's your name?

34:51.706 --> 34:54.071
--Heather.
--Jake.

34:55.916 --> 35:01.250
--Nice to meet you,
Jake. --You, too.

35:01.747 --> 35:02.560
Mommy!

35:03.288 --> 35:05.450
--I missed you so
much. --I love you.

35:12.747 --> 35:13.762
Hey, Buddy.

35:14.107 --> 35:16.401
Dad, there was
this deer...

35:19.476 --> 35:20.650
Mommy's right here.

35:20.795 --> 35:21.842
I'm right here, honey.

35:22.358 --> 35:23.710
Everything's
going to be okay.

35:26.057 --> 35:28.862
--Jake.
--Mom.

35:29.188 --> 35:31.811
--Oh, your face.
--I'll be all right.

35:31.815 --> 35:33.151
--Oh, honey.
--You okay?

35:33.397 --> 35:34.493
Of course.

35:35.156 --> 35:36.562
Eric, help your brother.

35:42.257 --> 35:45.571
--Put your arm around
me. --Careful. Careful.

35:50.485 --> 35:51.490
Easy. Easy.

35:52.407 --> 35:53.182
Okay.

35:53.498 --> 35:56.081
--Eric, get April. We'll meet
you the medical center. --Okay.

35:56.087 --> 35:58.772
Hey, hey, there's an
empty prison bus out there.

35:58.955 --> 36:01.090
--Whereabouts?
--Cedar Run.

36:01.365 --> 36:02.062
All right, just relax.

36:02.228 --> 36:03.113
I'll take care of it.

36:03.877 --> 36:07.362
--God! Look at you.
You're a mess. --It's fine.

36:07.368 --> 36:10.170
--Stop worrying about me.
--Well, good luck with that.

36:18.728 --> 36:19.932
Hey, Shep?

36:22.707 --> 36:25.391
You said earlier that you
had heard that speech before.

36:26.407 --> 36:28.503
Ever ask yourself
why I say it?

36:29.956 --> 36:31.361
'Cause I happen to
trust you people.

36:33.718 --> 36:34.841
'Cause I love my town.

36:36.285 --> 36:38.693
Now, something happened
in Denver, in Atlanta,

36:39.675 --> 36:41.293
and it could be
that we wake up

36:41.418 --> 36:43.122
and we find out that's
where it stopped.

36:43.496 --> 36:44.620
But, until we know,

36:45.796 --> 36:48.270
are we going to use our
imaginations to solve problems

36:48.275 --> 36:49.560
or to cause them?

36:53.197 --> 36:55.720
We can find out how
big this thing is.

36:56.588 --> 36:58.341
If we have to,
we can fight.

36:58.348 --> 36:59.203
We can fight anybody.

36:59.336 --> 37:01.000
We can fight all enemies.

37:02.445 --> 37:04.310
The only way that's
going to happen

37:04.316 --> 37:05.951
is if we work together.

37:08.307 --> 37:09.270
Now, go on home.

37:10.636 --> 37:13.473
We'll meet tomorrow
at the town hall.

37:15.736 --> 37:16.591
And, folks,

37:19.325 --> 37:21.231
don't you break
my heart again.

37:25.657 --> 37:32.270
Chief, keep all the men at their posts
until the sheriff gets back. Hey, Shep.

37:37.875 --> 37:40.130
I was afraid I was never
going to see you again.

37:42.045 --> 37:44.612
Come on. You think I'd
let Dad have the last word?

37:45.547 --> 37:46.402
Hey.

37:47.156 --> 37:48.330
Quit talking about me.

37:52.765 --> 37:54.673
You did a great thing
out there tonight.

37:56.755 --> 37:57.811
Thanks.

38:02.845 --> 38:04.601
Your grandfather
would have been proud.

38:11.965 --> 38:14.172
I'm going to go see what's
taking these guys so long.

38:20.737 --> 38:22.472
You know, I go
away for a few years

38:22.476 --> 38:24.192
and the town
goes to hell.

38:30.076 --> 38:31.552
I'm glad you're home.

38:33.547 --> 38:34.633
Yeah, we'll see.

38:46.096 --> 38:46.911
What are you thinking?

38:47.886 --> 38:50.640
I was just wondering what it was all
going to look like in the morning.

39:19.047 --> 39:24.422
(I'll sing it one
last time for you)

39:25.825 --> 39:30.381
(Then we really
have to go)

39:31.875 --> 39:36.700
(You've been the only
thing that's right)

39:38.158 --> 39:40.782
(In all I've done...)

39:40.486 --> 39:41.421
What's happening?

39:46.527 --> 39:49.291
(Light up, light up)

39:50.276 --> 39:55.221
(As if you have a choice)

39:55.578 --> 39:58.330
(even if you
cannot hear... )

